        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 5:11PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM CDT, radar was tracking a cluster of strong thunderstorms
near Ozona and extending southeast into western Sutton Counties.
The storms were moving slowly northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size to half inch size
hail. Heavy rain in a short period of time could cause
ponding of water on roads and minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The Intersection Of Ranch Road 1828 And Ranch Road 915, The
Intersection Of Us-
190 And Ranch Road 1828, The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163,
Eldorado, Us-277 Near The Sutton-Schleicher County Line, Ozona, I-10
Near The Crockett-Sutton County Line, Us-190 Near The
Crockett-Sutton County Line, and Sonora.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 348 and 411.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
